# Optional environment for the self-host Fluid build.
#
# Both stacks BUILD the Fluid images from source (amd64: docker-compose.redpanda.yml
# with the stock upstream Dockerfile; arm64: docker-compose.redpanda.arm64.yml with
# patched Dockerfiles), so there are no image tags to pin. By default the run-local
# helpers shallow-clone FluidFramework from GitHub into ./.fluidframework (gitignored)
# as the build source.
#
#   cp .env.example .env   # helpers load FLUID_REPO_DIR / FLUID_REF from this file
#
# Reuse an EXISTING FluidFramework checkout instead of cloning (point at the repo root):
# FLUID_REPO_DIR=../FluidFramework
#
# Pin a reviewed branch or tag in the helper-managed ./.fluidframework checkout (default for
# the first clone: main). On later runs, setting FLUID_REF fetches and checks out that ref again.
# Production releases must archive the resolved commit, local patch set, and resulting image
# digests. Use a branch/tag here rather than a raw commit SHA; see VALIDATION.md for the evidence
# boundary. When FLUID_REPO_DIR points to an existing checkout, select its revision yourself.
# FLUID_REF=main
